hbrellfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=277.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Culling begun</span><hr size=1> Tevesh walked through Nektulous after returning from Shadowhaven.  He removed his helm and scratched his head, trying to recall things that where blured beyond what it is normal for him.  Unbridled rage welled in his throat as he struggled through the muddled memories and the like.  A halfling ran past him in a hurry to get information back to the group that had taken up an outpost in the forest.  <br>
<br>
The unfortunate creature never new what hit him as Tevesh grabbed him and crushed his skull with his forhead.  Licking the blood as it flowed over his lips, he tossed the lifeless body down to the ground as he made his way back into Neriak.<br>
<br>
He quickly moved past the Trolls in the foreign quarter, wondering through the muck in his mind...&quot;When where there so many of them here?&quot;  Shrugging he continued down, rushing to the third gate to check on his family, something told him it was necessary to check on things, to make sure no one screwed anything up worse then Khasirath did by leaving.  &quot;The house's Golden Boy my arse&quot; he muttered under his breath as he turned down a side passage that would lead in through the servents quarters into the compound.<br>
<br>
Movement in the shadows caught his eye, without thinking (not that anyone would be surprised) he brought a mailed fist down on the back of the Tier'Dal's head.  Reaching down he looked over the Tier'Dal's belongings. The only thing that seemed to interest him was the wound up scroll.  Opening it he sat down on the still breathing body of the unnamed Tier'Dal and started trying to read the scroll.<br>
<br>
Ten minutes later he finished the scroll.  Casually he looked down at the body and wondered if he would wake up.  He took the scroll and threw it back down onto the Tier'Dal.  &quot;Obviously he was going to deliver it to me.  Oh well, this saves him the trip.&quot; he thought to himself.  Kicking the body over so it could breathe he continued into the compound.<br>
<br>
&quot;I'll b' th're ifn Dai'nus wants me 'r not.&quot; <p>My Magelo:&lt;br&gt;<br>
